------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. MAP FILE GENERATION
   - Generate ESMF/TempestRemap weight files for all component grids
   - EAM: ne30pg2 -> 1x1 (or target resolution)
   - MPAS-O/SI: oEC60to30 or oRRS18to6 -> 1x1
   - ELM: same as EAM if using same grid
   - MOSART: r05 -> 1x1
   - Store in E3SM inputdata repository for reproducibility

2. ELM/MOSART SOURCE FIELD LOOKUP
   - elm_fme_derived_update: needs field name -> ELM data type mapping
     (e.g., 'TSOI' -> temperature_vars%t_soisno_col)
   - elm_fme_vcoarsen_update: same — needs to read soil column data
   - rtm_fme_derived_update: needs field name -> rtmCTL member mapping
     (e.g., 'RIVER_DISCHARGE_OVER_LAND' -> rtmCTL%runofflnd_nt1)
   - These are case-by-case mappings, not generic — limited set of
     known fields that FME training needs

3. MPAS HORIZ REMAP INTEGRATION WITH ANALYSIS MEMBERS
   - The wrappers (mpas_ocn_fme_horiz_remap, mpas_seaice_fme_horiz_remap)
     are created but not yet called from the analysis member compute routines
   - Need to add remapped output writing to the analysis member streams
   - Challenge: remapped output has different dimensions (nlat x nlon)
     than native MPAS output (nCells) — may need separate streams

