REMAINING PRIORITY 2: Improvements for Better Production Use
------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. MPAS-O VERTICAL REDUCE: DYNAMIC REGISTRY FIELDS
   - Currently only built-in fields (OHC, FWC, KE) have Registry output vars
   - Generic user-configured reductions parsed from namelist but cannot be
     written without compile-time Registry variable definitions
   - Would need a fixed set of generic output slots (e.g., reduce_field_01..10)

5. STREAM OUTPUT FREQUENCY CONFIGURABILITY
   - MPAS analysis member output intervals are set in Registry XML
     (default daily). For production, may want 5-daily for ocean.
   - Can override via streams.ocean_forward in SourceMods/src.mpaso/
   - Consider adding namelist options for output interval

6. SINGLE PRECISION CONSISTENCY
   - MPAS stream output uses precision="single" (float32)
   - EAM cam_history uses default precision (double)
   - For FME training, float32 is preferred for all components
   - Verify EAM horiz_remap output uses single precision

